        "text": "It is not a new idea that permanent growth has no future. Many climate activists have long been convinced that nature can only survive if capitalism ends. So they have coined the catchy slogan: \"system change, not climate change.\" Nor is there any shortage of visions of what an ecological circular economy might look like, in which only as much is consumed as can be recycled. Keywords include the barter economy, the common good economy, consumerism, reduced working hours and an unconditional basic income."
