        "text": "However, some Germans also wonder whether it makes sense at all to think about climate protection on a national level. They fear that other countries might even take advantage if we reduce our greenhouse gases. For example, economist Hans Werner Sinn writes, \"Whether you think about coal, oil or natural gas, if Germany buys and burns less, then the Chinese can just buy and burn more.\" This mistrust is understandable, but it fails to recognize that almost all other countries are suffering from the climate catastrophe to an even greater extent than Germany. It is in their own interest to reduce greenhouse gases as well."
